page.title: 05WILDLIFE CONTINUED
page.content: {FOX:}MOSTLY NOCTURNAL. COMMON IN TILERY AND THORPE WOODS. FEEDS ON SMALL MAMMALS, ALSO INSECTS, SMALL BIRDS, EGGS, GRASS AND FRUIT. {BATS:}SEEN FLYING AROUND AT NIGHT, ROUND BUILDINGS AND WOODS. FEEDS ON INSECTS. {BADGER:}VERY VERY DIFFICULT TO SEE, ALMOST ENTIRELY NOCTURNAL. FEEDS ON EARTHWORMS, SMALL MAMMALS,CARRION, FRUIT, NUTS AND BULBS. {STOAT AND WEASEL:}BOTH ARE ACTIVE DURING DAY AND NIGHT. THE WEASEL FEEDS ON MICE AND VOLES, OTHER SMALL MAMMALS, BIRDS AND EGGS.
